The new species can be readily recognized by the following features: rostrum uniformly yellowish (
Fig. 9C
); hypovalves slender, with sparse short bristles along inner margins (
Fig. 10A
); parameres twisted in knee-shape, bearing long spines apically (
Fig. 10D
); dorsal valves of aedeagus brawny, expanded apically (
Fig. 10E
); main plate of medigynium flat, twice as long as wide, intensely constricted medially (
Fig. 10G
).

